---

# Enforce the strictest built-in rule set. The skip_list below exempts the
# few rules that clash with this project's documented house style.
profile: production

# Rules disabled because they conflict with this project's YAML house style:
#
# - yaml[indentation]: ansible-lint wants list items ('-') indented beneath
#   their key, but our convention aligns them with the key (no extra indent).
# - yaml[truthy]: we deliberately write booleans as 'yes'/'no' rather than
#   'true'/'false'.
#
# And one rule disabled to preserve the role's established variable interface:
#
# - var-naming[no-role-prefix]: the role's variables (stack_*, database_*, etc.)
#   are the documented interface used by AWX job templates and surveys. Prefixing
#   them all with 'fragalysis_stack_' would break that interface for no real gain.
skip_list:
  - yaml[indentation]
  - yaml[truthy]
  - var-naming[no-role-prefix]
